Explanation:
There are 7 vertices: 0–6.
Edges 0–1, 1–2, 2–3 form one connected group {0,1,2,3}.
Edge 4–5 forms another group {4,5}.
Vertex 6 is isolated (no incident edges), forming its own component.
So the connected components are:
{0,1,2,3}
{4,5}
{6}
Total components = 3.
